The manager of a detergent company rewards his employees for the number of detergent packets they sell in a month and hopes to keep them motivated. Instead of randomly determining who will receive the rewards, the manager uses a certain criteria on their sales. All the employees whose sales have odd number of factors greater than 4 are rewarded.

Input
The first line will contain an integer T as the number of test cases(1<=T<=10). Second line will contain the sales(integer N) of T employees where 1<=N<=100000.

Output
The output will contain T lines , 1 or -1 depending upon whether the employee is awarded or not.

Example

Input:
6
256 121 424 289 10609 7744

Output:
1
-1
-1
-1
-1
1
